variables:are used to define r declare some values in javascript.
	
	syntax: var variablename= 'value';
		var-is the reserved keyword to define the variable.
		variablename:-is the name of the variable where user is defining according to their needs.
	
	rules to define a variable name:
		1. it must be one word.
		2. it must consists only of numbers,letters,or underscores.
		3. it must not begin with a number.
		4. it should not contain any of the reserved keywords.

	local variables: variables which are declared inside the function and we 		cannot access local variables outside the function.

